<subSubSection box="[201,1199,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,358]" box="[201,1199,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,336,152,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name alludes to the word 
<taxonomicName authority="Kanarese" authorityName="Kanarese" box="[769,982,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="channa">
<emphasis box="[769,852,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">channa</emphasis>
(Kanarese)
</taxonomicName>
meaning beautiful.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,487,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="channa">
<emphasis box="[323,487,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Igerna channa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a well-developed anal collar process as in some species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1345,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Austroagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1345,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Austroagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the symmetrical aedeagus places it in the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[655,730,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[655,730,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1257,1331,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1257,1331,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Igerna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Oriental region by the presence of a process on the dorsal apodeme and a short tooth on the ventral projection of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,358]" box="[151,509,331,358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,509,331,358]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ishihara" authorityName="Ishihara" box="[238,509,331,358]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,396,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Japanagallia</emphasis>
Ishihara
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
